title: Grateful Dead Live at Hartford Civic Center on 1982-04-17

Set 1

Minglewood Blues-> Sugaree-> El Paso, Jack A Roe-> Little Red Rooster, Tennessee Jed, It's All Over Now, Bird Song-> Women Are Smarter

Set 2

Shakedown Street-> Lost Sailor-> Saint Of Circumstance-> Spanish Jam*-> Drums-> Space-> Uncle John's Band-> Not Fade Away-> Wharf Rat-> Around & Around-> One More Saturday Night

E: It's All Over Now Baby Blue

*Without Jerry

reviews.review_text: Good audience recording One of the first three bootlegs I got at age fifteen 35 years ago. This is the source right here. A few years later got the second set soundboard and always preferred this one. I'm a sucker for audience recordings...goes a long way in putting you there. I think the Sdb on this site has more audience in it than what I had years ago. Really good show. Love the Shakedown,Spanish jam and Wharf Rat...it's all good. Certainly worth the download. Thanks to everyone who makes it possible for us to access all these shows on archive. Hope it never goes away....peace.
